TRANS-PROVINCIAL
AIRLINES LTD.
SAFETY FEATURES OF YOUR DC-3
The
design
of
this
airplane,
the
continuing program of maintenance it
receives,
and the experience of your
captain and crew make it unlikely that
you will ever need to use the built-in
safety features of the DC3. However, it
is sound practice for every traveller to
be acquainted with them.
YOUR SEAT BELT is designed for your
comfort and safety in case of turbulence.
Please keep it fastened whenever the seat
belt sign is illuminated. You may find it
convenient to leave your seat belt loosely
fastened at all times and pull it snug when
the sign is lighted.
EMERGENCY EXITS
are clearly marked on both sides of the cabin. Instructions for opening them are printed on
each of these exits. Do not open an emergency exit unless requested by a member of your crew.
ESCAPE WINDOWS OVER WINGS
LOCATIONS
1. Pull cover open.
2. Grasp RED handle and
turn.
3. Entire window is then
outward.
4. Exit through window;
one leg first, then head
and shoulders, then the
other leg.
DOOR EXITS
WINDOW
EXIT
WINDOW
EXITS
Turn handle in direction of
drrow.
DOOR
EXIT
Push outward and down.
AFTER LEAVING AIRCRAFT
Proceed away from the aircraft in an orderly fashion to a safe distance in case of fire
- and keep together.
PLEASE READ OTHER SIDE
